LogFile.FinalText: An incredible likeness. That is how many people think about Denmark's two princesses. Mary and Marie are alike in many aspects, but different in just as many, if not more. They are both from abroad, born as common citizens and have found each their prince of Denmark - Mary is married to Crown Prince Frederik, and Marie to Prince Joachim. Also their names and appearances are remarkably similar. Both are beautiful as models and have long, dark hair and large, brown eyes. In spite of their many similarities, however, Mary and Marie are also two independent individuals who have lived and live in each their ways, and who have their own values and characters.
